com.paypal.merchant.sdk

Enum CardReaderManager.ChipAndPinConnectionStatus

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<CardReaderManager.ChipAndPinConnectionStatus>
      • com.paypal.merchant.sdk.CardReaderManager.ChipAndPinConnectionStatus
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<CardReaderManager.ChipAndPinConnectionStatus>
    Enclosing interface:
    CardReaderManager

    public static enum CardReaderManager.ChipAndPinConnectionStatus
extends Enum<CardReaderManager.ChipAndPinConnectionStatus>
    The list of possible status messages when initiating connection with a PayPal integrated Chip & Pin card reader.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      ConnectedAndConfiguring
      Indicates that the SDK was successfully able to connect to the terminal and is now getting the software version info of the same.
      ConnectedAndReady
      Device is connected and the software is up-to date - you are all set to begin taking payments with this reader.
      ConnectionInProgress
      Indicates that the SDK is trying to connect to an EMV terminal.
      Disconnected
      Indicates that the connection between the SDK and the EMV terminal is lost.
      ErrorBlockedCardReader
      Indicates that the bluetooth device is malicious/stolen/blackmarked
      ErrorBluetoothNotActiveListeningPort
      Indicates that currently SDK is not listening on Bluetooth port for swipers
      ErrorNewKeysRequired
      Indicates that the connected card reader requires a key update that will be performed now.
      ErrorSoftwareUpdateRecommended
      Indicates that a software update is available for this device.
      ErrorSoftwareUpdateRequired
      Indicates that the card reader requires a mandatory software update without which no further transactions are possible
      ErrorSoftwareUpdateTriedAndFailed
      Indicates that the Software update failed if it done as part of device connection
      ErrorUnknownCardReader
      Indicates that this bluetooth device is unknown
      InvalidStateError
      Indicates that we are in wrong state
      NotYetImplemented
      Your friendly neighborhood SDK dev is working on this one.
      SuccessWithWarning
      Indicates that there are items that need the user's attention but is not fatal yet to prevent usage
      TerminalInfoAvailable
      Indicates that the EMV terminal information such as the device name, OS version, Firmware version etc are now available and can be retrieved via the API : getEMVDeviceData().

      • ConnectedAndReady

        public static final CardReaderManager.ChipAndPinConnectionStatus ConnectedAndReady
        Device is connected and the software is up-to date - you are all set to begin taking payments with this reader.

      • SuccessWithWarning

        public static final CardReaderManager.ChipAndPinConnectionStatus SuccessWithWarning
        Indicates that there are items that need the user's attention but is not fatal yet to prevent usage

      • ConnectionInProgress

        public static final CardReaderManager.ChipAndPinConnectionStatus ConnectionInProgress
        Indicates that the SDK is trying to connect to an EMV terminal.

      • ConnectedAndConfiguring

        public static final CardReaderManager.ChipAndPinConnectionStatus ConnectedAndConfiguring
        Indicates that the SDK was successfully able to connect to the terminal and is now getting the software version info of the same. Along with this event, another similar event would also be emitted via the CardReaderListener.onPaymentReaderConnected() as well.

      • TerminalInfoAvailable

        public static final CardReaderManager.ChipAndPinConnectionStatus TerminalInfoAvailable
        Indicates that the EMV terminal information such as the device name, OS version, Firmware version etc are now available and can be retrieved via the API : getEMVDeviceData().

      • Disconnected

        public static final CardReaderManager.ChipAndPinConnectionStatus Disconnected
        Indicates that the connection between the SDK and the EMV terminal is lost. Along with this event, another similar event would also be emitted via the CardReaderListener.onPaymentReaderDisconnected() as well.

      • ErrorNewKeysRequired

        public static final CardReaderManager.ChipAndPinConnectionStatus ErrorNewKeysRequired
        Indicates that the connected card reader requires a key update that will be performed now. This error indicates that the reader cannot be used until this operation is performed

      • ErrorSoftwareUpdateRequired

        public static final CardReaderManager.ChipAndPinConnectionStatus ErrorSoftwareUpdateRequired
        Indicates that the card reader requires a mandatory software update without which no further transactions are possible

      • ErrorSoftwareUpdateRecommended

        public static final CardReaderManager.ChipAndPinConnectionStatus ErrorSoftwareUpdateRecommended
        Indicates that a software update is available for this device. While this update is not mandatory (yet) it is recommended that the update be performed nevertheless

      • ErrorUnknownCardReader

        public static final CardReaderManager.ChipAndPinConnectionStatus ErrorUnknownCardReader
        Indicates that this bluetooth device is unknown

      • ErrorBlockedCardReader

        public static final CardReaderManager.ChipAndPinConnectionStatus ErrorBlockedCardReader
        Indicates that the bluetooth device is malicious/stolen/blackmarked

      • ErrorBluetoothNotActiveListeningPort

        public static final CardReaderManager.ChipAndPinConnectionStatus ErrorBluetoothNotActiveListeningPort
        Indicates that currently SDK is not listening on Bluetooth port for swipers

      • ErrorSoftwareUpdateTriedAndFailed

        public static final CardReaderManager.ChipAndPinConnectionStatus ErrorSoftwareUpdateTriedAndFailed
        Indicates that the Software update failed if it done as part of device connection

      • InvalidStateError

        public static final CardReaderManager.ChipAndPinConnectionStatus InvalidStateError
        Indicates that we are in wrong state

      • NotYetImplemented

        public static final CardReaderManager.ChipAndPinConnectionStatus NotYetImplemented
